1. Shutdown DB (one node)
	oracle> srvctl stop database -d <dbname>
- Check: 
	oracle> srvctl status database -d <dbname>
2. Stop crs: (each node)
	root> ./crsctl stop crs -f
 - Check
	root> ./crsctl stat res -t

-----------------------------------
Open:
1. Start crs (each node)
	root> ./crsctl start crs
 - Check:
	root> ./crsctl stat res -t
2. Start database (one node)
	oracle> srvctl start database -d <dbname>
 - Check: 
	oracle> srvctl status database -d <dbname>
	oracle> srvctl listener database -d <dbname>
	(sqlplus / as sysdba)> select instance_name, status from gv$instance;
	(dgmgrl): show configuration -->> show database ...
	
-------------------------------------
 Auto start of Grid 
1. Check state crs
	root,grid> ./crsctl check crs
2. Check autostart
	root> ./crsctl config crs
	-->> Example result: CRS-4622: Oracle High Availability Services autostart is enabled.
3. Open autostart (each node)
	root> ./crsctl enable crs
4. Stop autostart (each node)
	root> ./crsctl disable crs

-------------------------------------
 Auto start of Database
1. Check state autostart of database
 srvctl config database -d <db_name>
2. 

[oracle@rac1 ~]$ srvctl status database -d orcl
Instance orcl1 is not running on node rac1
Instance orcl2 is not running on node rac2

[oracle@rac1 ~]$ srvctl start instance -d orcl -n rac1
[oracle@rac1 ~]$ srvctl status database -d orcl
Instance orcl1 is running on node rac1
Instance orcl2 is not running on node rac2

[oracle@rac1 ~]$ srvctl start instance -d orcl -i orcl2
[oracle@rac1 ~]$ srvctl status database -d orcl
Instance orcl1 is running on node rac1
Instance orcl2 is running on node rac2

---------------------------------------
Check list
1. Check state database
	(oracle)> srvctl status database -d <dbname>
	(oracle)> srvctl stop instance -d <dbname> -n <nodename>
	(oracle)> srvctl stop instance -d <dbname> -i <instance_name>
2. Check state autostart of grid
	(root)> ./crsctl config crs
3. Disable autostartof Grid
	(root)> ./crsctl disable crs
4. Stop crs in node 
	(root)> ./crsctl stop crs -f
5. Check state Grid after stop crs
	(root)> ./crsctl check crs
	(root)> ./crsctl stat res -t
